Mortal danger can count depending on case to case (under duress), stuff kinda like that. Just don't fucking LIVE in the land of lies. That's a great way to burn everyone and everything down (including yourself) without even PRINCIPLES to stand on.

snippet.textDisplay: Puppets in this game are created with a set of rules called the Grand Covenant. One of those rules is that puppets aren't allowed to lie. Pinocchio is a special puppet that was created by Geppetto after his dead son. Geppetto didn't impose the Grand Covenant on him, so he would better resemble a human being with free will. So Pinocchio is the only puppet than can lie. In this game, lying makes you human, and by lying throughout the game you gain humanity. With enough humanity, you can unlock the best ending - Rise of P. Also, all the lies you tell in the game are "good lies", to prevent other people from suffering.

I can see the argument for both paths but lying to a woman who is already on deaths door is the more empathetic and human thing to do. Would you tell a dying father their son had just been killed in an accident or lie and say he's still on his way but sends his love? 

If the woman were not dying then you have the choice to try and break a coping mechanism for a more healthy form of acceptance. But that is not the case, the woman is already dying and no alternative form of psychotherapy is available. As long as the lie does not then impact greater society in a detrimental way like say for example everyone starts believing her puppet is a real baby then lying would induce less suffering than telling the truth, especially in the short term; it is the more empathetic option.
